Reasoning: The paper deals with a problem of coordinating a swarm of autonomous mobile robots, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves forming a given target pattern, which can be seen as a problem of Distributed Systems (cs.DS) and Control (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a new notion of symmetricity in 3D-space, which can be seen as a contribution to Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper presents a pattern formation algorithm for oblivious FSYNC robots, which can be seen as a contribution to Concurrent, Distributed, and Parallel Computing (cs.CC).
